<subsection xml:id="lec-masPracticaEnRepresentarYResolver" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">

<shorttitle>Lección 20 </shorttitle>
<title>Lección 20 -<nbsp/></title>
<title>Más práctica en representar y resolver</title>


<!-- ============================================ 
  Objetivos de aprendizaje                        
=================================================  -->

<!-- Frase resumen para estudiante. Originalmente [Student Facing Goals] -->
<introduction component="est-goal"> 
  <p>Representemos y resolvamos más problemas.</p>
</introduction>

<!-- Objetivos para el estudiante. Originalmente [Student-Facing Targets] -->
<!-- <objectives component="estudiante">
  <ul>
    <li>[@@@@@@@@@@@@@@]</li>
  </ul>
</objectives> -->

<!-- Objetivos que solo ve el profesor. Originalmente [Teacher Facing Goals] -->
<objectives component="profesor">
  <ul>
    <li><p>[++++++++++++++++]</p></li>
    <li><p>Represent and solve two-step word problems.</p></li>
  </ul>
</objectives>


<!-- ============================================ 
  Introducción para el profesor                        
=================================================  -->
<introduction component="profesor">

  <!-- Estándares CCSS asociados -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="ccss-leccion-titulo"/></title> 
    <ul>
      <li> 
        <custom ref="ccss-addressing"/>        
        <xref ref="ccss-3-OA-C-7" text="custom">3.OA.C.7</xref>,
        <xref ref="ccss-3-OA-D-8" text="custom">3.OA.D.8</xref>
      </li>
    </ul>
    </paragraphs>

  <!-- índice de la lección (automático) -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="timeline-leccion-titulo"/></title>
    <list-of elements="subsubsection reading-questions" scope="subsection"/>
  </paragraphs>

  <!-- Propósito de la lección -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="purpose-leccion-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <p>The purpose of this lesson is for students to continue to represent and solve two-step word problems, including problems in which not all necessary information is given up front.</p>
  </paragraphs>

  <!-- Materiales requeridos -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="materials-leccion-titulo"/></title>
    <!-- <ul>
      <li>
        <p>Actividad 1</p>
        <xi:include href="./act-faltaInfo-introduccion-mat.ptx"/>
        <xi:include href="./act-faltaInfo-introduccion-matCentros.ptx"/>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>Actividad 2</p>
        <xi:include href="./act-faltaInfo-feriaDePasteleria-mat.ptx"/>
        <xi:include href="./act-faltaInfo-feriaDePasteleria-matCentros.ptx"/>
      </li>
    </ul>  -->
  </paragraphs>
  
  <!-- Introducción de la lección (narrative) -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="narrative-leccion-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <p>In this lesson, students continue to solve problems but encounter those that cannot be solved right away because of missing information. They learn the Information Gap routine, which prompts them to consider the information that is needed to solve a problem and ways to ask for it.</p>
    <p>The first activity introduces students to the routine. In the second activity, students are given more time to solve two-step word problems as they engage in the routine.</p>
  </paragraphs>
  
  <!-- Preguntas de reflexión profesor -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="reflection-quest-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <p>How did the Information Gap routine support students in making sense of two-step problems?</p>
  </paragraphs>
</introduction>


